Higher education and culture became new fronts in the struggle over power and memory. The Department of Education, under an earlier order, was being dismantled, and a coalition including the NAACP sued to stop the process. The Department\'92s Office for Civil Rights declared that Maine\'92s policy allowing transgender youth to play sports consistent with their gender identity violated Title IX, giving the state ten days to comply with the administration\'92s interpretation. Trump publicly demanded an apology from Maine\'92s governor for refusing to enforce his ban on trans athletes, casting her stance as an unlawful challenge to federal authority. In Texas, the state senate advanced bills that banned teaching about gender identity and sexual orientation, prohibited DEI policies in schools, criminalized the provision of \'93sexually explicit\'94 literature by educators, and mandated daily prayer or religious text readings and Ten Commandments displays in classrooms. These measures blurred the line between church and state and narrowed the space for inclusive civic education.\
