Information itself became both a weapon and a vulnerability. The week was dominated by revelations about a Signal group chat in which senior officials\'97including Vice President J.D. Vance, Defense Secretary Pete Hegseth, and National Security Adviser Mike Waltz\'97had discussed operational details of U.S. airstrikes in Yemen. A journalist, Jeffrey Goldberg of The Atlantic, had been inadvertently added to the chat and later published portions of it. The messages showed timing and deployment details for F\uc0\u8209 18s and other aircraft, as well as disparaging remarks about European allies and musings about economic gains from military action. The Pentagon had already warned staff against using Signal due to security vulnerabilities, but the president\'92s team had used it anyway for war planning. The gap between rhetoric and practice was stark.\
