Looking ahead from Week 10, several processes were already in motion. The emergency request to the Supreme Court on the Alien Enemies Act would force a confrontation over the balance between executive claims of national security and judicial insistence on due process. Lawsuits by major law firms against the executive orders targeting them would test whether the courts could protect the independence of the bar. The investigation requests from the Senate Armed Services Committee and the Defense Department\'92s inspector general into the Signal leak would reveal whether internal oversight could impose consequences on senior officials. The coalition suit to stop the dismantling of the Department of Education, and the academic lawsuits over student deportations, would shape the future of federal involvement in education and the rights of non\uc0\u8209 citizen dissenters. And the new election orders, if left in place, would begin to reshape voter rolls and ballot access well before the next national vote.\
