The week matters in the larger arc of the term because it shows how many fronts can be opened at once, and how each small advance toward midnight makes the next one easier. Courts, unions, journalists, and citizens still had tools to resist, and they used them. But the cost of resistance rose, and the space in which it could be effective narrowed. At 7:49 p.m., there was still time on the clock. The question left by Week 10 was not whether institutions existed, but whether they would be strong enough, and brave enough, to hold their ground as the pressure increased.\
